children.name: Visibility
children.doc: Show/hide the axes grid.

children.name: X Title
children.doc: Set the title string for X axis.

children.name: Y Title
children.doc: Set the title string for Y axis.

children.name: Z Title
children.doc: Set the title string for Z axis.

children.name: Faces To Render
children.doc:
Set the mask to select faces. The faces rendered will be a subset of the
          faces selected depending on the status of **CullBackface** and
          **CullFrontface** properties.

children.name: Cull Backface
children.doc:
Set to true to hide faces of the grid facing away from the camera i.e. hide all
              back faces.

children.name: Cull Frontface
children.doc:
Set to true to hide faces of the grid facing towards from the camera i.e. hide all
              front faces.

children.name: Grid Color
children.doc: Color used when coloring the grid wireframe

children.name: Show Grid
children.doc: Turn off to not render the plane grids.

children.name: Show Edges
children.doc: Turn off to not render the plane edges.

children.name: Show Ticks
children.doc: Turn off to not render the tick marks.

children.name: Label Unique Edges Only
children.doc:
Set to true to only label edges shared with 1 face. Note that
          if all faces are being rendered, this will generate no labels.

children.name: Axes To Label
children.doc:
Set the mask to select the axes to label. The axes labelled will be a subset of the
          axes selected depending on which faces are also being rendered.

children.name: X Axis Notation
children.doc: Get/set the numerical notation, standard, scientific or mixed (0, 1, 2) for X Axis.

children.name: X Axis Precision
children.doc: Get/set the numerical precision to use for the X Axis, default is 2.

children.name: X Axis Use Custom Labels
children.doc:
Specify whether to use custom labels for the X axis. Labels
          specified by **XAxisLabels** are used only when
          this flag is set to 1.

children.name: Y Axis Notation
children.doc: Get/set the numerical notation, standard, scientific or mixed (0, 1, 2) for Y Axis.

children.name: Y Axis Precision
children.doc: Get/set the numerical precision to use for the Y Axis, default is 2.

children.name: Y Axis Use Custom Labels
children.doc:
Specify whether to use custom labels for the Y axis. Labels
          specified by **YAxisLabels** are used only when
          this flag is set to 1.

children.name: Z Axis Notation
children.doc: Get/set the numerical notation, standard, scientific or mixed (0, 1, 2) for Z Axis.

children.name: Z Axis Precision
children.doc: Get/set the numerical precision to use for the Z Axis, default is 2.

children.name: Z Axis Use Custom Labels
children.doc:
Specify whether to use custom labels for the Z axis. Labels
          specified by **ZAxisLabels** are used only when
          this flag is set to 1.

children.name: Data Scale
children.doc:
If data is being scaled, you can show the original data bounds for the axes
          instead of the scaled bounds by setting the DataScale to match the scaling applied
          to the dataset.

children.name: Data Position
children.doc:
If data is being translated, you can show the original data bounds for the axes
          instead of the translated bounds by setting the DataPosition to match the
          translation applied to the dataset.

children.name: Data Bounds Inflate Factor
children.doc:
After the data bounds have been computed, this property enables to inflate the
          bounds used to generate the axes grid, so it will be slightly larger than the
          data bounds. It inflates the axes grid bounds using the diagonal length of the
          bounding box multiplied by this factor.
          Data bounds are not modified, only the aspect of the AxesGrid is modified.
          The default value (0.0008) ensures that there is no concident lines drawn when
          zooming close enough to the model.

ui.name: Center Axes Visibility
ui.doc:
Toggle the visibility of the axes showing the center of
        rotation in the scene.

ui.name: Hidden Line Removal
ui.doc:
Use a hidden line removal technique to hide wireframe surfaces that
          are occluded by other wireframe surfaces. Note that this is disabled
          when rendering distributed geometry in parallel.

children.name: Orientation Axes Visibility
children.doc:
Toggle the visibility of the axes showing the
        viewing direction.

children.name: Orientation Axes Interactivity
children.doc:
Allows repositioning of the orientation
        axes.

children.name: Use Light
children.doc: Enable/Disable the LightKit.

children.name: Light Switch
children.doc:
Turn on/off the default light in the 3D
        renderer.

children.name: Stereo Type
children.doc:
Set the stereo rendering mode to use. In client-server configurations,
          you may also want to set the ServerStereoType.

children.name: Server Stereo Type
children.doc:
This property allows you to set a different stereo mode for the server processes.
          Note that the stereo type selected on the client and server must be *compatible*, i.e.
          if the stereo type on the client side needs 2 renders each frame, the stereo type on the
          server must do exactly the same, otherwise deadlocks may ensue.

children.name: Enable OSPRay
children.doc: Switches between rasterization and ray tracing.

children.name: Shadows
children.doc:
Controls whether OSPRay casts shadow rays
        or not.

children.name: Ambient Samples
children.doc:
Sets the number of occlusion query rays that
        OSPRay sends at each intersection.

children.name: Samples Per Pixel
children.doc:
Set the number of primary rays that OSPRay
        shoots per pixel.

children.name: Progressive Passes
children.doc:
Set the number of render passes OSPRay takes to
        improve image quality. Has no effect unless ParaView
        is started with the --enable-streaming option.

children.name: Light Scale
children.doc: Dimish or Amplify all lights in the scene.
